mental densities and are only driven by galaxy mass. We infer that\nearly-type galaxy formation has undergone a phase transition a few billion\nyears ago around z~0.2. A self-regulated formation phase without environmental\ndependence has recently been superseded by a rejuvenation phase, in which the\nenvironment plays a decisive role possibly through galaxy interactions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Dec 2009 21:00:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 26 Jan 2010 15:47:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-14"}
